Uses of Class
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference.ReferenceBase

Packages that use ReferenceBase
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.jaxb   
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common Provides general technical or common classes on the base of which are built the model classes of all others thematic packages. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.description Provides classes: to describe specimens, observations or taxa, to associate other factual informations to specimens, observations or taxa (including distribution), to support identification by means of keys. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.media   
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.molecular Provides classes for DNA samples and related sequences. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.name Provides classes for nomenclature and typification. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference Provides classes for nomenclatural and bibliographical references either as a complex structure of specific subclasses according to the different kind of possible references used (see StrictReferenceBase class and subclasses) or as a flat structure (see BibTexReference class). 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon Provides classes for taxonomy including synonymy and concept synonymy. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.view   
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.strategy.cache.reference

Subclasses of ReferenceBase in eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference
 class Article
          This class represents articles in a journal.
 class BibtexReference
          This class represents references which are structured according to the BibTeX format.
 class Book
          This class represents books.
 class BookSection
          This class represents isolated sections (parts or chapters) within a book.
 class CdDvd
          This class represents electronic publications the support of which are Cds (Compact Discs) or Dvds (Digital Versatile Discs).
 class Database
          This class represents a database used as an information source.
 class Generic
          This class represents all references which cannot be clearly assigned to a particular reference subclass.
 class InProceedings
          This class represents isolated parts (usually papers or abstracts) within conference proceedings.
 class Journal
          This class represents journals.
 class Map
          This class represents published maps from which information can be derived.
 class Patent
          This class represents patents.
 class PersonalCommunication
          This class represents personal communications.
 class PrintedUnitBase
          This (abstract) class represents printed published references which are recurrent products of publishing companies or of research organisations.
 class PrintSeries
          This class represents collections of printed published references which are grouped according to topic or any other feature.
 class Proceedings
          This class represents conference proceedings.
 class PublicationBase
          This (abstract) class represents all different kind of published references which constitute a physical or virtual unit.
 class Report
          This class represents reports.
 class SectionBase
          This (abstract) class represents isolated sections (parts, chapters or papers) within a printed unit.
 class StrictReferenceBase
          This (abstract) class represents all different kind of references regardless of their peculiarities.
 class Thesis
          This class represents thesis.
 class WebPage
          This class represents electronic publications available on the world wide web.
